# Web CI — `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`

Pushes that touch `web/**` run **web-ci**: `lint` → `build` → `typecheck` → `test`.  
**Lint errors block merge** — especially `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`.

## Before commit or push (mandatory when `web/` changed)

```bash
cd web
pnpm lint        # must exit 0 — errors block CI
pnpm typecheck   # run after build if typedRoutes fails; see IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN §0
pnpm test        # when you changed components or tests
```

Do **not** commit or push web changes until `pnpm lint` is clean.

## The anti-pattern

Do **not** call `setState` synchronously inside `useEffect` to mirror other React state or props.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — fails eslint react-hooks/set-state-in-effect
useEffect(() => {
  setFormState(initial);
}, [open, data]);

useEffect(() => {
  setChildView(deriveFrom(parent));
}, [parent, askPrice]);
```

## Approved fixes

| Situation | Fix |
|-----------|-----|
| Display derived from props/state | `useMemo` during render — no effect |
| Reset local UI when session opens | Reset in `onOpenChange` / handler when `open` becomes true |
| Reset child when parent identity changes | `key={sessionId}` on child to remount |
| Seed local state once per session | `useState(() => seed)` + `key` when session changes |

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — derive
const maxbuyView = useMemo(() => buildView(view, laneAskPrice), [view, laneAskPrice]);

// ✅ GOOD — remount resets adjustments
<ResultBandAdjustments key={`${phase}-${odometer}`} defaultOdometer={odometer} />
```

## Agent checklist

1. After editing any `web/**/*.tsx`, scan new/changed `useEffect` bodies for `setX(` calls.
2. Refactor to derive, key, or event-handler reset **before** staging.
3. Run `cd web && pnpm lint` — fix all **errors** (not just warnings).
4. Only then commit/push.

More context: `docs/IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md` §0 (Pre-push CI gate).
